<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="399" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1896,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1896,1922]" pageId="3" pageNumber="399">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing darkly infuscated along veins, crossvein r-m nearly at 1/6 from apex of discal cell. Abdominal tergites anteriorly black with posterior band yellow. Epandrium irregular in shape, slightly wider than long in dorsal view; epiphallus elongate, with a very sharp apex in dorsal view, distiphallus spiny and slightly curved, acute at apex in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
